article.headline: Records scores 12, Colgate takes down Lehigh 63-60
article.description: — Keegan Records and Nicolas Louis-Jacques each hit two free throws in the final 15 seconds to allow Colgate to hold off Lehigh 63-60 on Saturday.
article.linkText: Records scores 12, Colgate takes down Lehigh 63-60
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- — Keegan Records and Nicolas Louis-Jacques each hit two free throws in the final 15 seconds to allow Colgate to hold off Lehigh 63-60 on Saturday. Records finished with 12 points and added 11 rebounds for the Raiders (22-9, 16-2 Patriot League). Braeden Smith scored 11 points while finishing 5 of 11 from the floor. Jeff Woodward shot 3 of 4 from the field and 4 for 4 from the line to finish with 10 points, while adding seven rebounds. Tyler Whitney-Sidney led the Mountain Hawks (12-17, 9-9) in scoring, finishing with 24 points and six rebounds. Dominic Parolin added 11 points and two steals for Lehigh. In addition, Keith Higgins Jr. had 11 points. Records put up eight points in the first half for Colgate, who led 35-25 at the break. Woodward led Colgate with six points in the second half as his team was outscored by seven points over the final half but held on for the victory. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
